      <div rendition="class:83225 maturity:83211" type="edition" xml:lang="san-Latn">
        <p><!--
Edition based on #Altekar_1947 with corrections from #Venkataramayya_1953. Restored text is based on %IN00217, except for bha of pratilambha and tiṣṭhā kr̥tā at the end, which is Altekar's conjecture.
--><lb n="1"/>siddhaM<supplied reason="subaudible">.</supplied> kr̥tayor dvayor vvarṣa-śatayor dvyaśītayoḥ <num value="282"><g type="numeral">200</g><g type="numeral">80</g> 2</num> caittra-pūrṇṇamā<choice>
            <sic>sīṁ</sic>
            <corr>syā</corr>
          </choice>m asyām pūrvvāyāṁ mahatā sva-śakti-guṇa-guruṇā pauruṣeṇa prathama-candra-darśa<unclear>nam iva mā</unclear><supplied reason="lost"><!-- CHECK if <unclear> applies better.-->lava-gaṇa-viṣayam avatāra</supplied><lb break="no" n="2"/>yitvaikaṣaṣṭi-rāttram atisattram aparimita-dharmma-māttraṁ samuddhr̥ttya pitr̥-paitāmah<choice>
            <sic>i</sic>
            <corr>ī</corr>
          </choice><sic>n</sic> dhuram āvr̥ttya suvipulaṁ dyāvāpr̥thivyor antaram anuttamena <unclear>yaśasā</unclear> <supplied reason="lost"><!-- CHECK if <unclear> applies better.-->sva-karmma-saṁpadayā vipulāṁ samu</supplied><lb break="no" n="3"/>pagatām r̥ddhim ātma-siddhiṁ vitatya māyām iva sattra-bhūmau sarvva-kāmaugha-dhārāṁ vasor ddhārām iva bbrāhmaṇāg<unclear>n</unclear>i-vaiśvānareṣu hutvā brahmendra-prajāpati-maharṣi-viṣ<unclear>ṇu</unclear>-<supplied reason="lost"><!-- CHECK if <unclear> applies better.-->sthāneṣu kr̥tāvakāśasya pāpa-ni</supplied><lb break="no" n="4"/>ravakāśasya sitasabhāvasatha-taḍāka-kūpa-devāyatana-yajña-dāna-sattya-prajā-vipula-pālana-prasaṅg<unclear>ai</unclear>ḫ purāṇa<surplus>ṁ</surplus>-rājarṣi-dharmma-paddhat<choice>
            <sic>ī</sic>
            <corr>i</corr>
          </choice>-satata-kr̥ta-samanugamana-niśca<supplied reason="lost"><!-- CHECK if <unclear> applies better.-->yasya sva-guṇātiśaya-vistarair manu</supplied><lb break="no" n="5"/>-nirvviś<choice>
            <sic>o</sic>
            <corr>e</corr>
          </choice>ṣam iva bhuvi manuṣya-bhāvaṁ yathārttham anubhavata Ikṣvāku-prathita-rājarṣi-vaṁśe mālava-vaṁśe prasūtasya jaya<unclear cert="low">tsena-naptur bhr̥gu</unclear>varddhana-pauttrasya jayasoma-puttrasya sogi<unclear cert="low">no</unclear><supplied reason="lost"><!-- CHECK if <unclear> applies better.-->naṁdisomasyāneka-śata-go-sahasra</supplied><lb break="no" n="6"/>-dakṣiṇā<supplied reason="subaudible">.</supplied> vr̥ṣa-pramatta-śr̥ṅga-vipradhr̥ṣṭa-cittya-vr̥kṣa-yūpa-saṁkaṭa-tīr<choice>
            <sic>o</sic>
            <corr>e</corr>
          </choice> puṣkara-ppratilam<supplied reason="lost"><!-- CHECK if <unclear> applies better.-->bh</supplied>a-bhūte sva-dharma-setau mahā<supplied reason="lost"><!-- CHECK if <unclear> applies better.-->taḍāke yūpa-pra</supplied><supplied cert="low" reason="lost">tiṣṭhā kr̥tā|</supplied><!--
L1. siddham is a little below the level of line 1. The halanta M is subscript, with a line above (which Altekar apparently takes for punctuation).
--><!--
L1. pūrṇṇa looks like tūrṇṇa in Halder's facsimile. My scan of the EI facsimile is useless.
--><!--
L3. There is an unnecessary stroke engraved to the left of the vertical of kā in kāmaugha, below the left side of the cross-stroke of k. (Altekar)
--><!--
L3. There is a concave semicircle above the anusvāra of dhārāṁ. (Altekar) This feature is discussed in #Altekar_1947:254.
--><!--
L3. There is an unnecessary dot before the s in vaso. (Altekar)
--><!--
L3. bbrā looks like pbrā (Altekar).
--><!--
L4. There is an unnecessary dot over bhā in sabhā.
--><!--
L4. kū in kūpa also has an o mātrā "through carelessness" (Altekar).
--><!--
L4. Altekar prints prasaṅgaf. I tentatively correct to prasaṅgaif, because the secondary inscription reads prasaṁgaiḥ and Altekar does not remark on this difference, so I assume a typo in his edition of the primary inscription. My scanned facsimile cannot help decide.
--><!--
L4. The unnecessary anusvāra of purāṇaṁ also has a semicircle above it (Altekar).
--><!--
L5. There is a concave semicircle above the anusvāra of both instances of vaṁśe. (Altekar)
--><!--
L5. I follow Venkataramayya's reading of the names. My scan is useless. Altekar reads jayanartana; followed by purbhāgravarddhana, em. prabhāgravarddhana; at the end he reads sogine, restoring soginetuḥ śrīsomasyā°. I wonder though, and should check if I ever get a chance: if Venkata is right that there are two characters before soma, can't it be bhaṭṭisoma like in the fragmentary inscription?
--><!--
L6. I retain Altekar's supplied daṇḍa after dakṣiṇā, but it seems unnecessary in light of the very plausible restoration of the end.
--><!--
L6. Altekar translates cityavr̥kṣa as "holy trees", probably taking it as equivalent to caityavr̥kṣa. I'm not sure. His translation is unconvincing in many places.
--></p>
